.SH NAME
copy_kernel_to_dynamic_supervisor \- Restore dynamic supervisor states from an xsave area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" copy_kernel_to_dynamic_supervisor
.BI "(struct xregs_state *xstate "  ","
.BI "u64 mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xstate" 12
A pointer to an xsave area
.IP "mask" 12
Represent the dynamic supervisor features restored from the xsave area
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only the dynamic supervisor states sets in the mask are restored from the
xsave area (See the comment in XFEATURE_MASK_DYNAMIC for the details of
dynamic supervisor feature). Besides the dynamic supervisor states, the
legacy region and XSAVE header are also restored from the xsave area. The
supervisor features in the XFEATURE_MASK_SUPERVISOR_SUPPORTED and
XFEATURE_MASK_SUPERVISOR_UNSUPPORTED are not restored.

The xsave area must be 64-bytes aligned.
